, at coffee time when we came in.  I could see it was getting my Mum and Dad down, more than myself because they were listening to it, about it, all day.  They had Radio {\*\xmlopen\xmlns1{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns1{\factoidname country-region
}}Cumbria{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} on all day and it just seemed to be one disaster after another and I think the more you listened to it the more down you get.  You know and I didn\rquote t tend listen to Radio {\*\xmlopen\xmlns1{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns1{\factoidname country-region}}Cumbria{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} partly because reception down here is no good.  You couldn\rquote t listen to it.   I had to put my ear to it, to the radio, to hear the outbreaks at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns1
